  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Creatives & Design Lead",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><ul><li>Own the creative direction and visual quality of assigned projects across events, digital, and brand campaigns.</li><li>Act as the creative lead and key client-facing representative on creative matters.</li><li>Conceptualise and execute creative ideas, from initial mood boards and mock-ups to final delivery.</li><li>Lead creative ideation and visual storytelling for new business pitches and proposals. Develop pitch decks, mood boards, concept visuals, and pre-visualisations.</li><li>Lead, manage, and develop the Company’s designers across graphic, motion, and 3D disciplines.</li><li>Set creative standards, workflows, and quality benchmarks across all projects.</li><li>Collaborate closely with Events, Media, and Digital teams to develop integrated creative solutions.</li><li>Guide and mentor designers, providing clear direction, feedback, and quality control.</li><li>Review and approve creative output to ensure consistency, accuracy, and high production standards.</li><li>Support pitches and proposals with creative concepts, visuals, and presentation materials.</li><li>Manage creative timelines and priorities in fast-paced, deadline-driven environments.</li></ul></p><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Digital Media / Arts / Design / Visual Communications or equivalent field.</li><li>Minimum 3 year working experience in relevant design field with proven team leadership experience</li><li>Strong pitch experience, including concept development and client presentations.</li><li>Good knowledge of related software skills in After Effects, Animate, Photoshop, Illustrator, Adobe XD, Adobe Premier Pro, Blender, Maya etc.</li><li>Good knowledge in video editing, animation and graphic design.</li><li>Ability to conceptualize and create design content.</li><li>Looking to grow into management position in future.</li><li>Possesses strong project management skills as some projects have tight deadlines.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
